The paper focuses on the retrieval-based question answering system, which is a common task in natural language processing. The use of BERT and tree structure for short sentence ranking is a technique that falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the use of Quora Question Pairs dataset suggests that the paper may also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) category, as the dataset involves image-related questions.
